Vice President Mike Pence will be delivering the commencement address at the University of Notre Dame on May 21, 2017. This will make him the first sitting Vice President of the United States to address the graduates during their commencement ceremony. Pence expressed his humility and excitement to return to his home state and address the graduates, acknowledging the impact they can make in the world. Notre Dame has a history of hosting distinguished speakers for their commencement ceremonies, including Presidents, Prime Ministers, journalists, military and government leaders, and scholars. During the ceremony, Pence will also be conferred with an honorary Doctor of Laws degree. Pence, who was born and raised in Indiana, has a background in law and politics, having served as a representative in the U.S. House and as the 50th Governor of Indiana before becoming Vice President.